Class ArrayQueue

  • java.lang.Object
    • domain.ArrayQueue
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SimpleQueue<HuffNode>

    public class ArrayQueue
extends java.lang.Object
implements SimpleQueue<HuffNode>
    SimpleQueue implementation for HuffNode elements that internally uses an array to store them.

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      ArrayQueue()
      Returns an instance of ArrayQueue that uses a newly created array to store the elements.
      ArrayQueue(HuffNode[] elements)
      Returns an instance of ArrayQueue prefilled with the elements of the given array.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Concrete Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean isEmpty()
      Returns true if the queue is empty (there are no elements in it), false if it has at least one element.
      boolean offer(HuffNode e)
      Tries to put the given element at the tail of this queue, returning true if successful, false otherwise.
      HuffNode peek()
      Returns the element at the head of this queue, without removing it.
      HuffNode poll()
      Returns the element at the head of this queue, removing it.
      int size()
      Returns the number of elements in this queue.

      • ArrayQueue

        public ArrayQueue(HuffNode[] elements)
        Returns an instance of ArrayQueue prefilled with the elements of the given array. It doesn't make a copy of the array, which can thus be modified by calls to this ArrayQueue's methods.
        Parameters:
        elements - An array containing the elements that will be used to fill the newly created ArrayQueue. It isn't copied, instead it's used directly.
